INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(264, 1, '2012-10-15 08:15:56', '2012-10-15 08:15:56', '<span class="quote" style="border: none !important;">"On the third day a wedding took place at Cana in Galilee. Jesus’ mother was there, and Jesus and his disciples had also been invited to the wedding. When the wine was gone, Jesus’ mother said to him, “They have no more wine.” “Woman, why do you involve me?” Jesus replied. “My hour has not yet come.” His mother said to the servants, “Do whatever he tells you.” Nearby stood six stone water jars, the kind used by the Jews for ceremonial washing, each holding from twenty to thirty gallons. Jesus said to the servants, "Fill the jars with water"; so they filled them to the brim. Then he told them, “Now draw some out and take it to the master of the banquet." They did so, and the master of the banquet tasted the water that had been turned into wine. He did not realize where it had come from, though the servants who had drawn the water knew. Then he called the bridegroom aside and said, "Everyone brings out the choice wine first and then the cheaper wine after the guests have had too much to drink; but you have saved the best till now." What Jesus did here in Cana of Galilee was the first of the signs through which he revealed his glory; and his disciples believed in him."</span> <span class="quoter">John 2:1- 11</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt is such a privilege and a blessing to be able to serve the Lord and His Kingdom through the ministry called the "Cantinas Ranch". The scripture from John Chapter 2 above is foundational to our goals and motivation. It is not our objective to understand all the "Whys?" when God asks us to do something, but try to be obedient to His instructions. We are called to walk by faith and not to lean on our own understanding. It is our desire to be active agents in providing opportunities where God can do the miraculous; where He can change water into wine. The number six and clay jars in scripture have both been used as symbols of man, and man being made of 98% water averaging between 10-13 gallons, could easily be a representative for the ceremonial pots set aside. His that are called, chosen, or set aside for His purposes, are to be filled with "living water", which will flow out of them like streams impacting and touching others. "Anyone who believes in me may come and drink! For the Scriptures declare, “Rivers of living water will flow from his heart." John 7:38\r\nWe believe that we, like the servants at the wedding, are called to be pot fillers! It is our desire to use the resources God has trusted us with to impact youth, families, Christian leadership, and our current culture. The vision of providing an extraordinary environment where faith is foundational, where instruction and programming is inspirational, and where lives can be transformed was the initial motivation for the Cantinas Ranch Camp Property. Since 2006, while waiting for the permitting and development of the property, exciting opportunities for the advancement of the foundation were initiated in the forms of Celebration of the Arts workshops, the Cantinas Music Festival, a National Worship Song Contest, the Broadway production "Scandalous", hosted Cantinas Ranch events at Lake Nacimiento, and establishment of the In The Word Community Outreach Ministry. It is the desire of our hearts that the Cantinas Ranch Foundation becomes an instrument; and one day a destination location, where the body of Christ will gather together in unity and with one voice worship the Lord. We entreat everyone to come drink the "living water" of God’s Word and purposes for their lives through the Cantinas Ranch Foundation programming. It will be His Spirit that will turn the water into wine; into the best wine that He has saved for last. Wine to be shared with others, in celebration of the King of kings, and His incredible love for us all!\r\n\r\nCelebrate!\r\nWendy and B. Wayne Hughes Jr.', 'Founders Letter', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'founders-letter', '', '', '2012-10-21 20:49:13', '2012-10-21 20:49:13', '', 6, 'http://10.0.1.9:8888/cantinasranch/?page_id=264', 0, 'page', '', 0);
